ervicenow-targets-over-30-billion-subscription-revenue-2030-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EServiceNow%20reported%20results%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20met%20or%20exceeded%20Wall%20Street%20expectations%20as%20the%20corporate%20software%20company%20grapples%20with%20concerns%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-ate-world-now-ai-eating-software-saas-anthropic-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI's%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20future%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubscription%20revenue%20rose%2025%25%20to%20%243.9%20billion%2C%20slightly%20ahead%20of%20TD%20Cowen's%20forecast%20of%20about%20%243.8%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20remaining%20performance%20obligations%2C%20a%20key%20measure%20of%20contracted%20future%20revenue%2C%20reached%20%2413.2%20billion.%20TD%20Cowen%20was%20looking%20for%20%2413%20billion%20in%20cRPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EServiceNow%20also%20raised%20its%20full-year%20subscription%20revenue%20guidance%20to%20a%20range%20of%20%2415.76%20billion%20to%20%2415.78%20billion.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20upper%20end%20of%20this%20forecast%20matched%20TD%20Cowen's%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stock%20popped%20more%20than%205%25%20in%20after-hours%20trading%2C%20following%20the%20results.%20However%2C%20the%20company's%20shares%20have%20slumped%2050%25%20in%20the%20past%20year%20amid%20concerns%20that%20generative%20AI%20could%20replace%20some%20corporate%20software%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20example%20of%20this%20arrived%20on%20Wednesday%20morning%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-presence-corporate-software-customer-service-sales-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20unveiled%20Presence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20new%20offering%20helps%20companies%20set%20up%20and%20run%20AI%20agents%20to%20help%20automate%20tasks%20such%20as%20customer%20support%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20resolving%20employee%20IT%20service%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20AI%20offerings%20like%20these%2C%20ServiceNow%20is%20building%20AI%20into%20existing%20products%20and%20rolling%20out%20new%20AI-powered%20offerings.%20The%20software%20company%20said%20its%20AI%20business%20surpassed%20%241%20billion%20in%20annual%20contract%20value%20during%20the%20second%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EServiceNow%20customers%20with%20AI%20agent%20deployments%20in%20production%20have%20increased%20ninefold%20over%20the%20past%20nine%20months%2C%20while%20the%20company%20said%20it%20signed%20123%20deals%20worth%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20in%20net%20new%20annual%20contract%20value%2C%20up%20nearly%2040%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Executive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fservicenow-ceo-dismisses-ai-threats-parlor-tricks-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBill%20McDermott%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20businesses%20increasingly%20need%20software%20that%20governs%20AI%20systems%20rather%20than%20simply%20running%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20positioned%20ServiceNow's%20AI%20Control%20Tower%20as%20a%20product%20that%20does%20exactly%20that%20by%20managing%20AI%20agents%20regardless%20of%20which%20model%20or%20chip%20corporate%20customers%20choose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESign%20up%20for%20BI's%20Tech%20Memo%20newsletter%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Ftech-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Reach%20out%20to%20me%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabarr%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabarr%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fservicenow-q2-2026-earnings-counter-ai-threat-narrative-strong-growth-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784751241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a61136454f98752617786a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fservicenow-q2-2026-earnings-counter-ai-threat-narrative-strong-growth-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ServiceNow%20reports%20Q2%20results%2C%20raises%20guidance%2C%20and%20says%20its%20AI%20business%20topped%20%241%20billion%20in%20annual%20contract%20value.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abarr%40businessinsider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mastercard's%20Jill%20Kramer%20says%20AI%20can%20be%20an%20engine%20of%20human%20creativity%20and%20insight%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jill%20Kramer%2C%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%2C%20Mastercard%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a54f78cd9d92978fe6a6adb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%227691%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJill%20Kramer%20joined%20Mastercard%20in%20December%2C%202025%3Cp%3EMastercard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJill%20Kramer%2C%20Mastercard's%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%2C%20was%20interviewed%20for%20the%20CMO%20Insider%20video%20series.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20spoke%20about%20the%20responsibility%20she%20feels%20in%20protecting%20the%20Mastercard%20brand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKramer%20said%20marketers%20should%20focus%20on%20how%20AI%20can%20enable%20them%20to%20do%20what%20they%20could%20not%20do%20before.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20debates%20over%20the%20role%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20in%20marketing%2C%20Jill%20Kramer%2C%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%20at%20Mastercard%2C%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20upside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20give%20ourselves%20permission%20to%20embrace%20the%20positive%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20video%20interview%20for%20CMO%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20see%20all%20that%20it%20could%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKramer%20joined%20Mastercard%20in%20December%202025%20as%20chief%20marketing%20and%20communications%20officer%2C%20after%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20at%20Accenture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20marketers%20need%20to%20give%20themselves%20permission%20to%20embrace%20the%20positives%20of%20AI%20because%20it%20can%20be%20an%20engine%20to%20foster%20creativity%20and%20deeper%20insights.%20Kramer%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20get%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-marketers-use-ai-test-creative-ideas-generate-insights-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eabout%20AI%20use%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20within%20the%20process%20of%20strategy%20and%20creativity%20does%20it%20fit%2C%20and%20where%20does%20it%20help%20you%20raise%20the%20bar%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20of%20the%20Mastercard%20brand%20was%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20drew%20Kramer%20to%20take%20on%20her%20new%20position.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20something%20that%20marketing%20does%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20that%20the%20entire%20company%20cares%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FpVuE1BjO-puACk8ZV.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20transcript%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223591dcc1-90a2-494e-bab1-fc5393585e6f%5C%22%3EThe%20brand%20belongs%20to%20everyone%20at%20the%20company%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strength%20of%20the%20brand%20is%20a%20bit%20mind-blowing%2C%20but%20it%20comes%20from%20something%20very%20simple%20and%20very%20true%3A%20Mastercard%20is%20a%20company%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frising-stars-of-brand-marketing-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecares%20deeply%20about%20its%20brand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20in%20the%20culture.%20It%20is%20not%20something%20that%20marketing%20does.%20It's%20something%20that%20the%20entire%20company%20cares%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20I%20made%20the%20move%20is%20because%20it%20was%20an%20incredible%20privilege%20to%20work%20for%20a%20company%20where%20I%20knew%20brand%20was%20everything%20to%20them.%20You%20do%20always%20wonder%20when%20you%20get%20inside%2C%20when%20you're%20behind%20those%20doors%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20that%20really%20what%20it's%20like%20from%20the%20inside%20out%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I'm%20very%2C%20very%20happy%20to%20say%20that%20it%20is.%20But%20we%20all%20know%20those%20brands%20that%20are%20something%20everyone%20loves%20and%20protects%20and%20nurtures%20and%20cares%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20that's%20one%20of%20the%20best%20things%20and%20one%20of%20the%20great%20privileges.%20With%20that%2C%20of%20course%2C%20comes%20great%20stress%20and%20responsibility.%20Everybody%20who%20has%20stewarded%20this%20brand%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20us%2C%20not%20just%20the%20person%20who%20sits%20in%20the%20my%20role%2C%20but%20everyone%20on%20the%20team%20%E2%80%94%20is%20making%20decisions%20that%20take%20the%20brand%20through%20that%20next%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20I%20care%20deeply%20about%20is%20giving%20ourselves%20permission%20to%20reflect%20back%2C%20to%20really%20understand%20where%20we%20are%20today%2C%20and%20define%20where%20we%20want%20it%20to%20go%20so%20it%20gets%20there%20intentionally%20and%20strategically%20and%20not%20accidentally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e3f2f15-3307-4111-adcb-807d50f00a39%5C%22%3EMarketers%20need%20every%20tool%20at%20their%20disposal%20today%2C%20including%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20feel%20like%20a%20lifetime%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20already%2C%20and%20it%20hasn't%20been%20that%20long.%20I%20think%20it%20was%20a%20privilege%20to%20be%20where%20I%20was%20when%20AI%20came%20onto%20the%20scene%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccenture-cmo-jill-kramer-talks-generative-ai-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eat%20Accenture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20a%20company%20whose%20whole%20focus%20is%3A%20What%20is%20the%20next%20wave%20of%20technology%20going%20to%20do%20to%20enterprise%20functions%2C%20industry%2C%20et%20cetera%3F%20It%20gave%20me%20a%20super%20early%20peek%20and%20permission%20to%20learn%20very%2C%20very%20early%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20biggest%20thing%20about%20AI%20is%20that%20we%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20debating%20whether%20it's%20the%20best%20thing%20or%20the%20worst%20thing%20to%20ever%20happen%20to%20marketing.%20I%20wish%20we%20would%20free%20ourselves%20of%20that%20construct.%20We%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraja-rajamannar-of-mastercard-on-the-biggest-challenges-facing-marketers-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eas%20marketing%20communications%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20know%20better%20than%20anybody%20that%20nothing%20is%20ever%20that%20clear-cut.%20It%20absolutely%20can%20be%20both.%20It%20very%20often%20is%20both%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20decisions%20that%20you%20make%20that%20decide%20which%20side%20of%20the%20path%20you're%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20that%20with%20the%20conditions%20we're%20facing%20in%20the%20world%20today%2C%20economic%20pressure%2C%20social%20pressure%2C%20global%20pressures%2C%20that%20we%20need%20every%20tool%20at%20our%20disposal%20to%20do%20the%20best%20potential%20marketing%20communications%20that%20we%20absolutely%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20absolutely%20a%20tool%20that%20can%20and%20should%20serve%20that.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20it%20as%20what%20AI%20does%20versus%20what%20we%20do%2C%20or%20at%20the%20efficiencies%20and%20headcount%20implications%20only%2C%C2%A0we're%20missing%20the%20ability%20to%20answer%20the%20question%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20else%20could%20I%20do%20that%20I%20could%20never%20do%20before%20because%20this%20tool%20now%20exists%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20there's%20some%20naivet%C3%A9%20built%20into%20that%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20give%20ourselves%20permission%20to%20embrace%20the%20positive%20first.%20Let's%20see%20all%20that%20it%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247a93163-5842-4b91-9b2a-2d3a3668a943%5C%22%3EAI%20can%20power%20human%20creativity%20and%20deeper%20insights%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-for-marketing-solo-business-client-outreach-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20as%20a%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20engine%20of%20driving%20creativity%2C%20it's%20really%20all%20about%20the%20breadth%2C%20the%20aperture%20that%20you%20can%20open%20up%20when%20you're%20doing%20your%20research%2C%20when%20you're%20doing%20your%20preparation%2C%20that%20will%20make%20the%20ideas%20flow%20and%20the%20creativity%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20recently%20in%20Japan%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20time%20to%20prepare%2C%20but%20the%20team%20there%2C%20the%20strategy%2C%20and%20the%20cultural%20deep-dives%20that%20we%20did%20were%20mind-blowing%20and%20so%20inspiring.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20was%20facilitated%20by%20the%20tools%20available%20today%20to%20gather%2C%20to%20distill%2C%20and%20to%20process%20so%20much%20content%20in%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20getting%20specific%20on%20the%20actual%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20and%20where%20within%20the%20process%20of%20strategy%20and%20creativity%20does%20it%20fit%2C%20and%20where%20does%20it%20help%20you%20raise%20the%20bar%3F%20The%20Japan%20workshop%20that%20I%20recently%20participated%20in%20was%20a%20great%20example%20of%20how%20we%20probably%20would%20have%20had%20a%20similar%20discussion%2C%20but%20with%20less%20breadth%20and%20less%20depth%2C%20had%20AI%20not%20been%20a%20tool%20that%20the%20team%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmastercard-cmo-jill-kramer-ai-marketing-strategy-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784751054000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a54f7aed9d92978fe6a6adc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmastercard-cmo-jill-kramer-ai-marketing-strategy-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mastercard's%20Jill%20Kramer%20says%20marketers%20need%20every%20tool%20at%20their%20disposal%2C%20and%20that%20AI%20can%20spark%20human%20creativity%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erica%20Iacono%2CJulia%20Hood)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Pompeii%3A%20Out%20of%20Time%20with%20Tom%20Hiddleston%E2%80%99%3A%20A%20Rare%20Doc%20That%20Could%20Actually%20Attract%20a%20Young%20Audience%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784750952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236818449%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202024%2C%20%E2%80%9CLoki%E2%80%9D%20star%20Tom%20Hiddleston%20reunited%20with%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20executive%20producer%20Kevin%20R.%20Wright%20to%20create%20a%20documentary%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20about%20a%20salacious%20murder%2C%20a%20cult%20or%20Hiddleston%E2%80%99s%20acting%20career.%20Instead%2C%20the%20duo%20set%20out%20to%20make%20a%20doc%20about%20Pompeii%20and%20the%20attempts%20of%20three%20real%20Romans%20to%20survive%20the%20ancient%20city%E2%80%99s%20final%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Addie%20Morfoot%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU