y%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-odyssey-christopher-nolan-review-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENolan's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20flattens%20Odysseus%20into%20a%20righteous%2C%20predictable%20hero%20with%20the%20reassuring%20face%20of%20a%20Hollywood%20sweetheart.%20Sigh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20let%20me%20clarify%3A%20I'm%20not%20a%20book-to-movie%20adaptation%20snob%2C%20especially%20not%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20an%20ancient%20text%20spun%20from%20myth%20and%20folklore.%20Many%20scholars%20believe%20the%20epic%20poem%20we%20know%20as%20Homer's%20was%20actually%20composed%20by%20multiple%20people%20and%20reshaped%20over%20time%3B%20it%20would%20be%20weird%20if%20Nolan%20%3Cem%3Edidn't%3C%2Fem%3E%20take%20artistic%20liberties%20or%20update%20the%20story%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-odyssey-early-morning-showtimes-imax-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emodern%20audiences%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20how%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey%26quot%3B%20was%20created%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20a%20filmmaker%20is%20going%20to%20omit%20or%20subvert%20huge%20chunks%20of%20the%20source%20material%2C%20those%20changes%20should%20serve%20a%20greater%20purpose.%20They%20should%20make%20the%20story%20more%20interesting%2C%20more%20legible%2C%20or%20more%20thematically%20effective.%20Some%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-odyssey-christopher-nolan-release-date-trailer-cast-details-2026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENolan's%20biggest%20changes%20to%20Odysseus%3C%2Fa%3E%20do%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223074%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Director%20Christopher%20Nolan%20with%20Matt%20Damon%20and%20Zendaya%20on%20the%20set%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5e8432ce52cb26b839188d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222049%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDirector%20Christopher%20Nolan%20with%20Matt%20Damon%20and%20Zendaya%20on%20the%20set%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Sue%20Gordon%2FUniversal%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECasting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatt-damon-odyssey-role-lifestyle-change-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMatt%20Damon%20as%20Odysseus%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20first%20hint%20that%20Nolan's%20title%20character%20may%20not%20be%20quite%20the%20antihero%20depicted%20in%20the%20source%20material.%20Though%20Damon%20has%20played%20complicated%20characters%20before%20%E2%80%94%20a%20CIA%20assassin%2C%20a%20rat%20for%20the%20Boston%20mob%2C%20a%20psychopathic%20con%20artist%20%E2%80%94%20at%20its%20core%2C%20Damon's%20status%20as%20a%20movie%20star%20is%20rooted%20in%20his%20perceived%20wholesomeness.%20He%20plays%20Odysseus%20as%20an%20honorable%2C%20salt-of-the-earth%20warrior%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20guy%20who%20plucks%20his%20bow%20while%20hunting%20to%20give%20his%20prey%20a%20fair%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDamon's%20performance%20embodies%20the%20character's%20noblest%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20king%2C%20husband%2C%20war%20hero%20%E2%80%94%20while%20shunning%20his%20dark%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe5975ac-3dca-4898-bb91-1512d32ad5bd%5C%22%3E'Wily%20Odysseus%2C%20the%20lord%20of%20lies'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOdysseus'%20dark%20streak%20makes%20him%20more%20interesting%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20driving%20force%20in%20the%20poem's%20plot.%20Why%20does%20it%20take%20an%20experienced%20seafarer%2010%20years%20to%20make%20it%20home%20after%20the%20Trojan%20War%2C%20you%20may%20ask%3F%20A%20few%20strokes%20of%20bad%20luck%2C%20of%20course%2C%20and%20divine%20intervention%20plays%20a%20role%20%E2%80%94%20but%20mostly%2C%20Odysseus%20is%20a%20scalawag%20who%20causes%20as%20many%20problems%20as%20he%20solves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOdysseus%20spends%20years%20satisfying%20his%20appetites%20and%20whims%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20his%20crew%20and%20his%20waiting%20family%20back%20in%20Ithaca.%20He%20has%20a%20sexual%20relationship%20with%20the%20sea%20nymph%20Circe%2C%20which%20turns%20a%20brief%20stop%20for%20supplies%20into%20a%20yearlong%20sidequest%2C%20and%20with%20the%20goddess%20Calypso.%20When%20he%20first%20washes%20up%20on%20the%20shore%20of%20the%20latter's%20island%2C%20he's%20hardly%20desperate%20to%20leave%20her%20lush%20paradise.%20True%2C%20after%20seven%20years%20with%20her%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20go%20home%20because%20Calypso%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20pleased%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20also%20means%20at%20one%20point%2C%20she%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOdysseus%20is%20smart%2C%20but%20his%20ego%20makes%20him%20short-sighted.%20He%20famously%20can't%20help%20but%20take%20credit%20for%20his%20cunning%20escape%20from%20the%20Cyclops.%20He%20taunts%20the%20monster%2C%20telling%20him%20precisely%20who%20to%20blame%20for%20his%20humiliation%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BOdysseus%2C%20the%20city-sacker%2C%20Laertes'%20son%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Ithaca%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20brings%20the%20vengeance%20of%20Cyclops'%20father%2C%20the%20sea%20god%20Poseidon%2C%20crashing%20down%20on%20himself%20and%20his%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20includes%20none%20of%20these%20unflattering%20details.%20The%20hero's%20selfish%20edges%20are%20buffed%20until%20a%20smoother%2C%20sturdier%20figure%20remains.%20In%20the%20movie%2C%20Odysseus%20never%20cheats%20on%20his%20wife%2C%20at%20least%20not%20consciously.%20He%20only%20spends%20so%20much%20time%20with%20Calypso%20because%20she%20feeds%20him%20memory-erasing%20lotus%20flowers.%20While%20he%20does%20offend%20Poseidon%20by%20shooting%20the%20Cyclops%20with%20an%20arrow%2C%20it's%20framed%20as%20an%20impulsive%20lapse%20in%20judgment%2C%20not%20an%20indictment%20of%20his%20hubris%20and%20deception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20Odysseus'%20dark%20side%20causing%20him%20to%20make%20pivotal%2C%20repeated%20mistakes%2C%20he%20mostly%20comes%20across%20as%20an%20unlucky%20guy%20trapped%20in%20a%20cruel%2C%20illogical%20world.%20Oh%2C%20look%2C%20he's%20landed%20on%20another%20island%20with%20magical%20creatures%20trying%20to%20kill%20him!%20Bummer!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223074%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matt%20Damon%20as%20Odysseus%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5e8474ce52cb26b839188f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222049%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Damon%20as%20Odysseus%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMelinda%20Sue%20Gordon%2FUniversal%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20Nolan's%20Odysseus%20is%20finally%20able%20to%20confront%20Penelope's%20suitors%20%E2%80%94%20the%20men%20who%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20marry%20his%20wife%2C%20plotting%20to%20murder%20his%20son%2C%20and%20feasting%20his%20family%20out%20of%20house%20and%20home%20%E2%80%94%20he%20seems%20reluctant%20to%20exact%20his%20revenge%2C%20sheepish%20and%20ashamed%20of%20the%20cycle%20of%20violence%20he's%20helped%20perpetrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20presented%20as%20a%20moment%20of%20reckoning%20in%20Nolan's%20film.%20Odysseus%20is%20haunted%20by%20the%20Trojan%20Horse%2C%20his%20bespoke%20trick%20to%20breach%20the%20city%20of%20Troy.%20It%20won%20the%20war%2C%20but%20it%20was%20such%20a%20brazen%20violation%20of%20Zeus'%20hospitality%20law%20that%20it%20sent%20psychic%20shockwaves%20through%20time%20and%20space.%20Odysseus%20becomes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-career-of-j-robert-oppenheimer-father-of-atomic-bomb-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elike%20the%20ancient%20Oppenheimer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eclipsed%20by%20the%20consequences%20of%20his%20own%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20of%20Nolan's%20most%20inspired%20revisions%2C%20but%20the%20hero's%20climactic%20epiphany%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bto%20burn%20the%20walls%20of%20Troy%20was%20to%20burn%20the%20world%20entire%2C%26quot%3B%20lands%20slightly%20left%20of%20satisfying%20when%20Odysseus%20has%20been%20presented%20as%20a%20good%20guy%20from%20the%20start%20%E2%80%94%20not%20as%20a%20guy%20who's%20gradually%20been%20forced%20to%20confront%20his%20own%20evil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20story%2C%20Odysseus%20still%20needs%20to%20kill%20the%20suitors%2C%20or%20else%20leave%20his%20wife%20and%20son%20in%20their%20clutches.%20He%20immediately%20atones%20for%20the%20mass%20murder%20by%20going%20into%20self-imposed%20exile.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20the%20good-guyification%20of%20Odysseus%20hadn't%20already%20been%20clear%2C%20the%20movie%20ends%20with%20our%20hero%20sailing%20off%20into%20the%20sunset.%20No%2C%20really.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-odyssey-christopher-nolan-movie-changes-from-book-odysseus-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784749993000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5e4996548c9c486b30e14f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-odyssey-christopher-nolan-movie-changes-from-book-odysseus-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Christopher%20Nolan's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Odyssey%26quot%3B%20stars%20Matt%20Damon%20as%20a%20noble%20and%20heroic%20Odysseus.%20It's%20a%20change%20from%20Homer's%20original%20character.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cahlgrim%40insider.com%20(Callie%20Ahlgrim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paramount%2B%20is%20moving%20into%20micro%20dramas%20as%20Hollywood%20falls%20in%20love%20with%20short%20video%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221382%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22P%2B%20microdrama%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a61087b54f987