ips%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20is%20most%20bullish%20on%20Nvidia%20and%20Broadcom%2C%20but%20memory%20makers%20are%20catching%20up.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20says%20it's%20worth%20sticking%20through%20the%20roller%20coaster%20ride%20in%20memory%20stocks%2C%20and%20that%20any%20selling%20creates%20a%20good%20entry%20point%20for%20investors.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-stocks-bear-market-ai-sk-hynix-sndk-mu-wdc-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMemory%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20seen%20huge%20swings%20lately%2C%20with%20the%20Roundhill%20Memory%20ETF%20falling%20into%20a%20bear%20market%20before%20the%20stocks%20it%20tracks%20rebounded%20this%20week.%20Morgan%20Stanley%20analyst%20Joseph%20Moore%20says%20investors%20should%20look%20at%20bouts%20of%20selling%20as%20an%20opportunity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRecent%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20second%20derivative%20deceleration%2C%20higher%20capex%2C%20de-speccing%20%E2%80%94were%20predictable%20a%20month%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20to%20investors.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20is%20not%20a%20normal%20cycle%20%E2%80%94%20memory%20is%20a%20bottleneck%2C%20increasingly%20THE%20bottleneck%2C%20to%20AI%20builds%20(and%20agentic%20CPU%20builds)%2C%20which%20appear%20durable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20memory%20trade%20has%20become%20crowded%2C%20exacerbating%20the%20swings%20over%20the%20last%20few%20weeks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20also%20noted%20that%20investors%20may%20be%20misreading%20a%20critical%20detail%20of%20the%20broader%20market.%20The%20consumer%20electronics%20sector%20is%20currently%20facing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbudget-smartphone-market-expected-decline-memory-shortage-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esignificant%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20rising%20component%20costs%20and%20sluggish%20demand%20forecasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Moore's%20view%2C%20that%20may%20be%20making%20the%20memory%20market%20appear%20weaker%20than%20it%20actually%20is%2C%20since%20the%20data%20center%20buildout%20is%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20memory%20boom%2C%20not%20PCs%20and%20smartphones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20spending%20growth%20north%20of%2050%25%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20well%20north%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20processor%20company%20commentary%2C%20matters%20more%20each%20year%20as%20AI%20is%20a%20bigger%20portion%20of%20the%20pie%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20has%20seen%20several%20boom-bust%20cycles%20for%20AI%20chips%2C%20but%20Moore%20maintains%20that%20this%20time%20is%20likely%20different%2C%20given%20how%20much%20memory%20demand%20has%20surged%20in%20recent%20months.%20He%20cited%20the%20fact%20that%20DRAM%20(Dynamic%20Random-Access%20Memory)%20is%20starting%20to%20limit%20how%20fast%20companies%20can%20expand%20as%20evidence%20of%20its%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20analysts'%20view%2C%20there%20simply%20isn't%20enough%20DRAM%20to%20go%20around%20right%20now%2C%20and%20with%20data%20centers%20fueling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ai-data-center-power-electricity-use-consumption-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeven%20more%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20memory%20makers%20are%20well-positioned%20to%20keep%20growing%2C%20creating%20opportunities%20for%20investors%20willing%20to%20play%20the%20long%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analyst%20also%20noted%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20memory%20boom's%20timeline%2C%20his%20team%20is%20focused%20more%20on%20duration%20of%20the%20boom%2C%20as%20several%20years%20of%20strong%20earnings%20would%20be%20better%20than%20one%20year%20of%20quick%2C%20unsustainable%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20that%20the%20selloff%20in%20the%20stocks%20has%20created%20a%20strong%20entry%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20think%20that%20the%20best%20value%20in%20the%20market%20comes%20from%20the%20compute%20names%2C%20notably%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fnvda-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Favgo-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBroadcom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20memory%20is%20catching%20up%20quickly%20given%20this%20deceleration%2C%20and%20we%20think%20this%20should%20provide%20a%20good%20entry%20point%20for%20the%20stocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20isn't%20the%20only%20Wall%20Street%20bank%20that%20says%20investors%20should%20stick%20with%20the%20AI%20hardware%20trade.%20Analysts%20from%20Bank%20of%20America%20and%20UBS%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchip-stocks-ai-hardware-kimi-k3-ubs-bofa-wall-street-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esaid%20this%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20sector's%20volatility%2C%20memory%20demand%20remains%20robust%20and%20the%20AI%20bull%20narratives%20are%20largely%20intact.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-chip-stocks-selloff-buy-the-dip-nvda-avgo-mu-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784736572000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a60d03dce52cb26b839254c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-chip-stocks-selloff-buy-the-dip-nvda-avgo-mu-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Morgan%20Stanley%20says%20selling%20in%20memory%20stocks%20is%20an%20opportunity%2C%20as%20demand%20for%20memory%20capacity%20from%20data%20centers%20continues%20to%20create%20bottlenecks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Police%20formal